The values of `x0` and `x1` are computed by iterating over the tree; their value is no longer infinity after iterating; instead they are the minimum and maximum node x-value. Initializing `x0` and `x1` to ±Infinity simplifies the computation of the minimum and maximum values. It’s the same reason `Math.min()` (with no arguments) returns Infinity and likewise `Math.max()` returns -Infinity.

```js
